1.0 Introduction

According to a study from the National Council on Crime and Delinquency in 20061, the United States has come to rely on jail as a reaction to all sorts of crime in the last 30 years. Minor infractions of parole or probation frequently result in a return to prison. This has resulted in a massive jail system in the United States. The research also mentions interesting facts about incarceration in the United States: - The United States is home to the world’s largest prison population. - The incarceration rate in the United States is four times that of the rest of the world. - Some US states imprison up to six times the number of individuals as countries with similar populations. - The United States has the highest rate of female incarceration in the world. - Incarceration rates are not taken into account when calculating crime rates.
